parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the loss of power steering, brake by wire, and other critical systems, leading to a loss of vehicle control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Sudden and simultaneous warning lights
loss of power steering
brake by wire failure
speedometer failure
airbag and restraint system failure
and inability to turn off the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The hybrid battery can catch fire while the vehicle is parked and charging, causing damage to the vehicle and surrounding property, and potentially harming occupants.
symptoms: Spontaneous combustion of the hybrid battery
flames shooting out from the hood
and total loss of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle can shut down unexpectedly, leaving occupants stranded and potentially at risk of serious health problems or even death.
symptoms: Vehicle shuts down when the driver's door is opened
leaving occupants in a potentially life-threatening situation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delays in recall repairs can leave vehicles on the road with known safety issues, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Parts unavailable for recall repairs
dealers unable to schedule repairs
and manufacturers failing to provide timely solutions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The drivetrain malfunction can cause the vehicle to lose power, slow down, or accelerate unexpectedly, leading to accidents or unsafe driving conditions.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly slows down
loses power
or accelerates unexpectedly; the drivetrain malfunction warning message appears on the dashboard; the vehicle is unable to shift into gear or maintain speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause accidents, injuries, or damage to property, as the vehicle may suddenly move forward without the driver's input.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly without warning; the vehicle revs or lurches forward when the driver takes their foot off the brake pedal; the vehicle moves independently while in reverse gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Power supply issues can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or malfunction, leading to accidents or unsafe driving conditions.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly loses power or stalls; the power supply warning message appears on the dashboard; the vehicle's systems
such as the air conditioning
malfunction or become hot to the touch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission and gear shifting issues can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or malfunction, leading to accidents or unsafe driving conditions.
symptoms: The vehicle has difficulty shifting into gear; the vehicle loses power or stalls; the transmission warning message appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Cross Traffic Alert System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear cross traffic alert system can lead to accidents or near-misses while reversing, as the driver is not alerted to approaching vehicles or pedestrians, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: No visual or acoustic alert from the rear cross traffic alert system while reversing
inadequate warning
or warning only when the vehicle is inches from another vehicle or pedestrian
failure to detect approaching vehicles or pedestrians.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inadequate rear lighting can reduce visibility while reversing, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Insufficient lighting to view surroundings behind the vehicle
especially at night.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration and brake failure can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities, especially when combined with the failure of safety monitoring features.
symptoms: Vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
brakes are unresponsive
failure of safety monitoring features
such as collision warning and obstacle detection systems.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Software Glitch in Lock/Unlock and Side Mirror Deployment System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning software can cause the side mirrors to deploy unexpectedly, obstructing the driver's view while backing up or changing lanes, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The side mirrors deploy unexpectedly
sometimes only one mirror deploys
the lock/unlock system does not function correctly
requiring multiple attempts to lock or unlock the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Forward Sensors and Braking System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the forward sensors and braking system can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities, as the vehicle may not stop in time to avoid obstacles.
symptoms: The forward sensors do not activate the braking system
the vehicle fails to stop or slow down
resulting in accidents or near-misses.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden explosion of the sunroof can cause injuries, damage to the vehicle, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: A loud explosion-type sound
followed by glass falling from the sunroof
the sunroof shatters without any apparent cause.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Drive Train Warning and Power Loss
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The drive train warning and power loss can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The drive train warning light appears
followed by power loss and stalling
the vehicle may lose power while driving on the highway.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Software Glitch Causing Vehicle to Shut Off
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The software glitch can cause the vehicle to shut off unexpectedly, leaving occupants without air conditioning, which can be life-threatening in extreme temperatures.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts off when the driver's door is opened
ignoring the menu selection to not shut off
the air conditioning stops working
leaving occupants without a cooling system.
